China Approves $400 Million for Qualified Foreign Investors

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-29T11:13:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/china-approves-400-million-for-qualified-foreign-investors-1-.html
China  has approved $400 million in
quotas for four Qualified Foreign Institutional Investors,
according to a statement on the State Administration of Foreign
Exchange’s website today.  The regulator also approved $1.585 billion in quotas for
three Qualified Domestic Institutional Investors, the statement
said, bringing total approvals to $20.69 billion for 103
institutions by end of today.  In the first four months, China approved $2.985 billion
worth of QDII quotas to invest overseas, exceeding the $970
million for the QFII amount, it added.  “The country will continue to process qualified
institutional investors in an orderly and steady manner
according to China’s international balance of payments
situation,” the statement said.  --Feiwen Rong. Editors:  Richard Dobson , Abhay Singh  To contact the reporter on this story:
